%[main]
\page{
  \font{DejaVuSerif}{28}

  This application computes an approximate solution to the dispersion
  of \link{volcano}{volcano ash} \link{volcano}{over Europe}
  \link{volcano}{after an} \link{volcano}{eruption.} Input data are set
  interactively and results are computed instantaneously.

  \par

  \link{numerics}{Numerical simulations} are used in geophysical
  applications like weather forecast or in predicting the propagation
  of pollutants in the atmosphere. \link{equation}{Mathematical models}
  that describe these phenomena are usually expressed in terms of Partial
  Differential Equations (PDEs). Computing solutions to systems of PDEs
  is a challenging task.
}
\hint{link:manual}{Learn how to use this program}{7.66}

